The "SANS critical security controls" is a framework developed by the SANS Institute to provide organizations with a prioritized and structured approach to cybersecurity. It is a set of 20 security controls that are considered to be essential for any effective cybersecurity program. The controls are organized into three categories: Basic, Foundational, and Organizational.

The SANS critical security controls can be related to other topics such as cybersecurity frameworks, risk management, incident response, vulnerability management, and security awareness training.

